\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {12}{\ignorespaces Watermark evasion analysis across three strategies at increasing intensity. The unigram z-score defense maintains $\text  {TPR}=1.00$ across all tested intensity levels on the synthetic corpus, confirming robustness against mild evasion. More aggressive strategies (large $\rho $ or high character-swap budget) that would reduce $\text  {TPR}$ also visibly degrade the adversarial passage quality.}}{23}{figure.caption.73}\protected@file@percent }
